Description: 
Following on from the superb Great Writers: in Their Own 
Words, this new series delves deep into the archives to 
produce a potted history of late 20th-century thinkers. 
Unlike their forebears, latter-day intellectuals abandoned 
ivory towers and embraced new science programmes like 
Horizon to share their theories. Episode one begins with 
the boffins who revolutionised how we thought, beginning 
with a rare radio broadcast by Sigmund Freud recorded 
mere months before his death.
